# Project overview

**vibe-squire** is a local background orchestrator that polls GitHub for PRs requesting your review and syncs them as Kanban issues into Vibe Kanban via its **local HTTP API**.

## Tech stack

- **Runtime:** Node.js >= 20 (LTS)
- **Framework:** NestJS 11 (modules, DI, lifecycle hooks, schedulers, HTTP/SSE)
- **Database:** SQLite via Prisma (with `@prisma/adapter-better-sqlite3`)
- **Vibe Kanban:** `fetch` to the desktop app's local HTTP API (`apps/server/src/vibe-kanban/rest/`)
- **GitHub:** `gh` CLI via `child_process`
- **Validation:** Zod (`@vibe-squire/shared`, env/schemas), class-validator (legacy DTOs), `nestjs-zod` on selected REST responses
- **UI:** React + Vite SPA in `apps/web/` (Nest serves `dist/client`); operator BFF under `/api/ui/*`
- **Logging:** Pino via `nestjs-pino`
- **Testing:** Jest, `@nestjs/testing`, Supertest

## Directory layout

```
apps/server/           — Nest app (`vibe-squire` npm package)
apps/web/              — Vite + React operator UI
packages/shared/       — Zod contracts (`@vibe-squire/shared`)
apps/server/src/
├── config/            — Zod env schema, AppEnv token, EnvModule
├── database/          — SQLite path resolution, SQLite migration runner
├── prisma/            — PrismaModule (client provider)
├── generated/prisma/  — Generated Prisma client (do not edit)
├── ports/             — Port interfaces and DI tokens (hexagonal boundary)
├── integrations/
│   ├── github/        — gh CLI scout, PR search schema, GitHub settings
│   └── vibe-kanban/   — HTTP board adapter, VK settings
├── sync/              — Poll scheduler, dispatcher, reconciliation, poll-cycle
├── settings/          — SettingsService, key-value CRUD, effective precedence
├── mappings/          — Repo → project mapping CRUD
├── status/            — Aggregate health endpoint, SSE stream
├── events/            — Domain event bus (StatusEventsModule)
├── setup/             — Setup-complete gate
├── reinit/            — Soft reinit endpoint
├── ui/                — Operator BFF (`/api/ui/*`), activity API, nav aggregation
├── logging/           — Pino logger configuration
├── app.module.ts      — Root module (AppModule.forRoot)
├── main.ts            — Bootstrap: env parse → migrate → create app → listen
apps/server/test/      — Integration specs (*.integration-spec.ts)
apps/server/prisma/    — schema.prisma + migrations
docs/                  — Architecture documentation
apps/server/bin/       — CLI entry point (vibe-squire.js)
```

## Naming conventions

- **Files:** kebab-case (`poll-scheduler.service.ts`, `github-pr-scout.service.ts`)
- **Classes:** PascalCase with NestJS suffixes (`PollSchedulerService`, `SyncController`)
- **Port interfaces:** Defined in `apps/server/src/ports/`, named `*Port` (e.g. `SyncPrScoutPort`, `DestinationBoardPort`)
- **DI tokens:** UPPER_SNAKE Symbols in `apps/server/src/ports/injection-tokens.ts`
- **Tests:** `apps/server/src/**/__tests__/**/*.spec.ts` (unit), `apps/server/test/*.integration-spec.ts` (integration)
- **Settings keys:** snake_case strings matching Prisma `Setting.key`

## Key patterns

- `AppModule.forRoot(env)` is the only valid way to boot the module graph. Never use bare `AppModule`.
- Integration adapters are registered dynamically by `IntegrationsModule.register(env)` based on `VIBE_SQUIRE_SOURCE_TYPE` / `VIBE_SQUIRE_DESTINATION_TYPE`.
- Settings follow env > SQLite > code-default precedence (`SettingsService.resolveEffectiveSetting`).
- The sync pipeline is guarded: setup must be complete, `gh` authenticated, and the Vibe Kanban API probe must succeed before polls run.
- SSE pushes status snapshots on material state changes (poll start/end, settings change, reinit).
